    "body": "I'm kind of having the same problem with respect to this issue.\r\n\r\nSo here's what happen.\r\n\r\nI have a set of html files that are predominantly using handlebars in another platform. \r\nIn my current express setup, I'm using ejs to include 'header', 'footer' or any other html snippet files.\r\n\r\nNow I wish to do the following:\r\n\r\n`const express = require(\"express\");`\r\n`const engines = require('consolidate');`\r\n`app = express();`\r\n`app.engine('html', engines.handlebars);`\r\n`app.engine('html', engines.ejs);`\r\n\r\n`app.get(\"/\", function (req, res) {`\r\n`res.render(\"index\", context); //index page here will go through handlebars and populate the necessary markdown with properties in context and go through ejs for the include syntax to work`\r\n`});`\r\n\r\nSo that the the request will go through handlebars -> ejs when the view is rendered.\r\n\r\nApparently, this is not working. express can only recognise ejs.",
