    "body": "The original source is from another platform. (think PHP style includes with Handlebars syntax for dynamic content).\r\n\r\nI would very much prefer to use a handlebars-style \"include\" if they do have it but what they have, Partials, seems to be only good if you want to reuse components on the same page.\r\n\r\nI don't mind doing:\r\n\r\n**index.html**\r\n{{ include header.html }}\r\nSome content {{Username}}\r\n{{ include footer.html }}\r\n\r\nbut I don't think the vanilla version of handlebars supports the above. Any 3rd party library will have to be vetted for as it is a commercial project so it's not easy to use any random libraries. (license issues, support, etc.)",
