    "body": "In handlebars with that syntax 'include' is just a helper named include - from the aforementioned link. You can make 'helpers' for whatever you want in handlebars which makes it really super useful. \r\n\r\nIt works really well, as its quite a simple premise and keeps things pure. Perhaps take a look and investigate what can be done with those tools and the other handlebars extensions available.\r\n\r\nI think mixed-mode document rendering is like, the worst thing I can think of haha #iminhell #pleasesaveme so I wouldn't hold your breath on getting such a thing given to you.\r\n\r\nYou could ofcourse write your own view engine and apply both of these directly inside it's handlers.",
